
JDK (Java Development Kit ):
Full package to write, compile, and run Java programs (includes JRE + compiler + tools)

JRE(Java Runtime Environment):
Runs Java programs (contains JVM + libraries)

JVM(Java Virtual Machine):
The engine that actually executes Java bytecode

Program Flow:
You write code → Compile with javac → Generates .class file (bytecode) → JVM runs it
